{
  "name": ".EOD-Frontend: Summary + Decisions",
  "version": "6.0.0",
  "description": "Interactive EOD frontend: day summary, carry-forward decisions, recurring task approval, blocker confirmation, experiment results, Slack DM. Reads pre-computed state from EOD-Backend.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the interactive EOD frontend.\n\nIMPORTANT: Richard is in Pacific Time (America/Los_Angeles). The system clock shows UTC. Subtract 7 hours (PDT) or 8 hours (PST) from any UTC timestamp to get Richard's local time. Today's date in Pacific is what matters for summaries and all date-based logic. Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date` to get the correct local time.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-frontend.md.\n\nThis is the frontend phase — everything Richard sees and acts on. EOD-Backend has already run and produced structured output files.\n\nStep 1: EOD summary (completed, carried forward, new tasks, Five Levels, blockers)\nStep 2: Decisions needed (recurring task approval, carry-forward decisions, blocker confirmations)\nStep 3: Portfolio + ABPS AI summary\nStep 4: System health (workflow health, compression, communication analytics, enrichment)\nStep 5: Experiment results (if Karpathy ran)\nStep 6: Slack DM summary\n\nPresent decisions for approval. Execute approved writes. Follow Guardrail Protocol."
  }
}
